    <abstract>
      <t>This document describes how Kerberos V may be used in order to allow a DHCP client and server to mutually authenticate as well as to protect the integrity of the DHCP exchange. The protocol described in this document is capable of handling both intra-realm and inter-realm authentication.</t>
